			<p><div class="thumb-right"><a href="images/suc_img/year2_1.png"><img src="images/suc_img/year2_1.png" /></a>Every dwarf in the fortress helped smooth the stone of Overload's study.</div><span style="font-family: 'Glass Antiqua', cursive; font-size: 48px;">O</span>n the 27th day of Granite, early Spring 252, a migrant named Overload came with a wave of thirty-one souls to the fortress. He made quick work of getting into the fortress and immediately found his clay housing deplorable, so within the season had named himself manager of the fortress and ordered the dwarves under his rule to build him a massive study. Our excavation seems to be concluding that the remains of this journal were discovered within the rubble of Overload's study.</p>
			<p><span style="font-family: 'Glass Antiqua', cursive; font-size: 48px;">O</span>n the 17th of Slate, mid Spring of the same year, Overload noted that the first baby boy was born under his rule. Why he chose to note this as his first entry into the chronicle remains puzzling - perhaps it was Overloa's child (legitimate or not) and thus an achievement in his life.</p>
