			<p><div class="thumb-right"><a href="images/suc_img/year2_2.png"><img src="images/suc_img/year2_2.png" /></a>The Metalsmithing Hub.</div><span style="font-family: 'Glass Antiqua', cursive; font-size: 48px;">T</span>he fragments are torn, but the next notation happens on the 3rd of Felsite, in late spring. Overload appears to be building now and has ordered construction of a metalsmithing hub. He plans to burn wood, get fuel, smelt metal, and make weapons. He also makes a quick note on the 5th of Felsite that the room designations are "shitty" and orders it "fixed" - he notes here that this is "boring" - this historian again pauses to marvel at the man's hubris and wonder why he took the time to note such a menial task when he, himself, pens that the task is boring. He is undertaking grand construction, yet trifling in room banality - and writing about it. This seems puzzling.</p>
